To customize the Nginx log output template and apply the custom template format to the access.log file, you can use the `log_format` directive in the Nginx configuration file. For example:

```nginx
http {
    ...
    log_format my_custom '$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] '
                         '"$request" $status $body_bytes_sent '
                         '"$http_referer" "$http_user_agent"';
    access_log /path/to/access.log my_custom;
}
```

In this example, the `log_format` directive defines a custom log format named `my_custom`, and the `access_log` directive specifies the log file and the custom log format to use.

